### OVERVIEW

## Support
This app does not include any support. Please use splunk answers, or Splunk-Usergroups Slack and consult general Splunk documentation

#### About the TA_trendmicro_cef_CIM

| Author | Bharat Jindal |
| --- | --- |
| App Version | 1.0.0 |
| Vendor Products | Trend Micro Apex Central |
| Has index-time operations | true |
| Create an index | false |
| Implements summarization | false |

The TA_trendmicro_cef allows a Splunk® Enterprise administrator to easily extract and parse CIM compatible fields from the Trend Micro Apex Central software logged in CEF format

#### Release notes
This TA was built specifically for CEF data from Trend Micro Apex Central software and designed with the Malware Data Model in mind.

##### About this release

Version 1.0.0 of the TA_trendmicro_cef_CIM is compatible with:

| Splunk Enterprise versions | 6.x, 7.x, 8.x |
| --- | --- |
| CIM | 4.10 |
| Platforms | Platform independent |
| Vendor Products | Trend Micro Apex Central (CEF Logs)|
| Lookup file changes | none |

#### Splunk Enterprise system requirements

Because this add-on runs on Splunk Enterprise, all of the [Splunk Enterprise system requirements](http://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/latest/Installation/Systemrequirements) apply.

#### Configure TA_trendmicro_cef_CIM

You may need to adjust the eventtypes.conf search to include your index=. Otherwise this TA is plug and play. Deploy to Indexers and Search Head(s), or if your data is sent to a Heavy Forwarder, install to HF and Search Head(s)

## USER GUIDE

### Data types

This app provides the index-time and search-time knowledge for the following types of data from Trend Micro Apex Central (CEF):

trendmicro

Description and example

These data types support the following Common Information Model data models:

- malware

